						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: Rājakēsarivarman (Rājarāja I) Year 17: 1002 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This record is fragmentary. It begins with the <hi rend="italic">mēykīrtti</hi> of the king Rājarāja I, <hi rend="italic">‘Tirumagaḷ pōla’.</hi> It probably records an endowment made by a lady inorder to feed a brāhmaṇa well-versed in vēdas, at the temple in Tiruvoṟṟiyūr. Reference is made to a village Karikālapākkam.</p>						

						</summary>
